		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />You said &quot;faux-hexagonal&quot; but it looks to me like the actual topology is indeed hexagonal, even though the tiles are square in shape.<br /><br />If you did actually want them to appear hexagonal, you could achieve the shape by putting some gaps between the tiles. They won't be touching edge to edge anymore, but they can at least have the hex shape this way without being a problem for the attributes.<br /><br />If you'll pardon me for drawing over your art, I was interested in trying a few variations out:<br /><div class="attachtitle">Attachment:</div><div class="attachcontent">
			<img src="./download/file.php?id=10755" alt="aethelion_hexagonal_mask0.png" /><br />
